A nice Omakase experience in Hong Kong, I was surprised by the freshness of the seafood, even though Hong Kong is well known for its seafood, this was particularly good. It’s a bit pricey but a worth while experience, happy diner 😋
Ate like 30 items during this 3 hour course. So many rare and expensive seasonal fish included in this $1500 omakase. So much better than Michelin Omakase!!
One of the best omakase in town :-) Food is fresh and chef has explained to us the best way to taste each dish! Some rare seafood to taste and we have 20+ dishes that night. Great experience.

reviews.text: 食物質素是上品的，但加上環境、份量、服務和價值，可以有太多其他選擇！1500 + 10%
Omakase is not cheap given the service and layout, but the food served are at most mediocre. I dislike the oyster mostly, which was not fresh.
小小的店舖，衹有8個位，但做出超水準，值得讚!

高質日式料理，每次都入日本各地當做食材。8座位店裡簡潔，三個幾鐘食二十品。重點 - 師傅對每一品想達到既味道和口感都直接傳達到俾客人。整體來說好滿意既一個美食體驗。

One of the highest quality Japanese food in HK. Ingredients are sourced and flown from different regions in Japan. 
Clean store layout with 8 counter seats, ate 20 types of delicacies in over 3 hours.
Each dish were thoughtfully prepared to serve the chef's philosophy, which is to serve as best as he can.
Overall a great dining experience.
Geart food here and the chief is super decent and professional! Highly recommended 👍🏻
